From {{inh|en|enm|pigge|t=pig, pigling}} (originally a term for a young pig, with adult pigs being {{m|enm|swine}}), apparently from {{inh|en|ang|*picga}} (attested only in compounds, such as {{m|ang|picgbrÄ“ad|t=mast, pig-fodder}}). Compare {{cog|dum|pogge}}, {{m|dum|puggen}}, {{m|dum|pegsken|t=pigling}}.

